  "text": "On the other hand, removal rates of total nitrogen of the four CW systems were quite low (24%-35%). Denitrification process was usually considered to be limited under high oxygen concentration condition, resulting in high ammonium removal rate but low TN reduction in VSSF CWs [CITATION_1] . On the contrary, though denitrification was suggested to be faster in horizontal subsurface flow than that in vertical flow, removal rate of ammonium and TN were both low in HSSF CWs in this work because of the restriction of nitrification process, as shown in Table 2 .",
